article.headline: S. Dakota 74, New Orleans 66
article.story: NEW ORLEANS -- Jesse Becker scored 27 points, including seven 3-pointers, to lead South Dakota to a 74-66 win over New Orleans on Sunday. Tyler Cain added 22 points and 11 rebounds to help the Coyotes (9-5) pick up their first win over a Division I school since 1979. South Dakota, which is a transitional D-I member, was 0-3 against D-I schools this season. T.J. Worley led the Privateers (5-7) with 22 points, including a 4-for-8 mark from 3-point range, and added a career-high 11 rebounds. Besides Worley, the Privateers combined to go 0-for-10 from beyond the arc. Kyndall Dykes added 14 points and Jaroslav Tyrna had 12. New Orleans trailed 53-43 with 12:29 to play in the game, but the Privateers went on a 19-8 run during the next 7:33 to grab a 62-61 advantage near the five-minute mark. South Dakota then outscored the Privateers 13-4 in the final 4:56.
